Now I see the issue. In `TSEnumDeclaration::write`:

```rust
write!(f, ["enum", space(), self.id(), space(), "{", self.body(), "}"]);
```

This writes `{self.body()}` on the same line. The body handles the empty case with `soft_line_break()` for the dangling comments, but the closing `}` is directly appended after the body without a newline.

Compare with `TSInterfaceBody::write`:
```rust
write!(f, [space(), "{"]);
if self.body.is_empty() {
    write!(f, format_dangling_comments(self.span).with_block_indent());
} else {
    write!(f, block_indent(&self.body()));
}
write!(f, "}");  // <-- `}` is written after a newline
```

The issue is that in `TSEnumDeclaration::write`, the `}` is part of the same write as the body. When the body is empty with dangling comments, the soft_line_break creates the newline, but `}` follows right after the body in the same write statement, and there's no newline between the closing comment and `}`.

